; map
INUMBER 1578
NAME 1060
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
SUBSTANCE PAPER
*DESCRIPTION_START READ
You carefully examine the map...
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB READ -1
     CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER    Deep Realms -- Surface Entrance. As Recorded by Menelian the Sage.
     ECHO PLAYER                                 X..# <-ladder
     ECHO PLAYER                                    .
     ECHO PLAYER                                     .
     ECHO PLAYER                                      . ...
     ECHO PLAYER                                       .. .
     ECHO PLAYER                                               .
     ECHO PLAYER                                                 .
     ECHO PLAYER                                                 --
     ECHO PLAYER                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~||~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
     ECHO PLAYER                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~||~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
     ECHO PLAYER                       ~~~~~~                    --
     ECHO PLAYER                    ~~~~r
     ECHO PLAYER                 ~~~~a
     ECHO PLAYER             ~~~~m
     ECHO PLAYER          ~~~~n
     ECHO PLAYER        ~~~i
     ECHO PLAYER      ~~~t                                      Fayd
     ECHO PLAYER    ~~~l                                         |
     ECHO PLAYER ~~~ E                                          \|/
     ECHO PLAYER ~~                                               S%c
     ECHO PLAYER The map describes a precise crevice to enter through to reach a cave.
     EQUAL INTNUM25 1
ENDIF
;
INUMBER 1579
NAME 1059
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 1000
*DESCRIPTION_START
The cottage is constructed of mirmach logs and has a thatched roof. Some smoke rises from its chimney. Gazing through the window, you see that it is pretty messy inside. An oak door allows entrance.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
;
VARIABLE MADEMEN
;
MNUMBER 291
UNIQUE
NAME Menelian
ETERNAL
HUMAN
WEAPON 544 -1 10
BODY 5
EXTRABODY 20000
ATTACK1 10
DEFENSE 1000
RESIST 1000
STRATEGY 1
GENDER 0
ALIGNMENT 200
*DESCRIPTION_START
Menelian is an ancient, frail human. His head is almost completely bald,
but a few white hairs still persist around the edges. He has a scraggly
white beard that dangles down to his waist. He squints at you through
some fine silver spectacles, and wears a simple wool robe.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
;
; cottage door
INUMBER 1580
NAME 72
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 1000
PORTAL
HIDDEN
OPENABLE
IFPREVERB GO -1
	  EQUAL DUMMY1 RNUM
	  AFFECT 1802
          SETITEMVAL 7 2 DUMMY1
          SETITEMVAL 8 2 DUMMY1
          IFVAR MADEMEN = 0
		EQUAL MADEMEN 1
		GENMON 291
	  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
VARIABLE COTPLACE
;
CEVENT 43 250 128
EQUAL DUMMY1 0
IFVAR COTPLACE = 0
      AFFECT 128
      ECHO ALL Suddenly, a cottage appears out of nowhere!
      EQUAL COTPLACE 1
      NEWITEM 8 1579
      NEWITEM 7 1580 VAL2=1802 ADJ1=447
      EQUAL DUMMY1 1
ENDIF
IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
      IFVAR COTPLACE = 1
	  AFFECT 128
	  ECHO ALL Suddenly, the cottage vanishes!
	  REMOVEITEM 8
	  REMOVEITEM 7
	  AFFECT 156
	  ECHO ALL Suddenly, a cottage appears out of nowhere!
	  NEWITEM 8 1579
	  NEWITEM 7 1580 VAL2=1802 ADJ1=447
	  EQUAL COTPLACE 2
	  EQUAL DUMMY1 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
	IFVAR COTPLACE = 2
		AFFECT 156
		ECHO ALL Suddenly, the cottage vanishes!
		REMOVEITEM 8
		REMOVEITEM 7
		AFFECT 944
		ECHO ALL Suddenly, a cottage appears out of nowhere!
		NEWITEM 8 1579
		NEWITEM 7 1580 VAL2=1802 ADJ1=447
		EQUAL COTPLACE 3
		EQUAL DUMMY1 1
	ENDIF
	IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
		IFVAR COTPLACE = 3
			AFFECT 944
			ECHO ALL Suddenly, the cottage vanishes!
			REMOVEITEM 8
			REMOVEITEM 7
			AFFECT 128
			ECHO ALL Suddenly, a cottage appears out of nowhere!
			NEWITEM 8 1579
			NEWITEM 7 1580 VAL2=1802 ADJ1=447
			EQUAL COTPLACE 1
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
      ENDIF
ENDIF
;
VARIABLE MENTALK
;
NUMBER 1803
NAME Menelian's Cottage, Dark Corner
RELOGIN 1802
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This dark corner accords some measure of privacy in Menelian's cottage.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
	EQUAL MENTALK 0
	IFVAR INTNUM27 ! 2
		IFVAR INTNUM26 > 0
			EQUAL INTNUM27 2
			ECHO PLAYER Menelian joins you.%c
			ECHO PLAYER You tell Menelian all about your adventures in the Deep Realms, and finally what Instadtoo told you about the meaning of life.%c
			ECHO PLAYER Menelian sighs. "Ah, well," he says. "Perhaps this is a wonder not meant for us to comprehend. Thank you for sharing with me the stories of your other adventures in the Deep Realms."%c
			AWARD 14 20000
			IFVAR LEV > 20
				AWARD 15 20000
			ENDIF
			IFVAR LEV > 30
				AWARD 16 30000
			ENDIF
			IFVAR LEV > 40
				AWARD 16 30000
			ENDIF
			EQUAL MENTALK 1
			ECHO PLAYER Menelian pats you on the back.%c
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	IFVAR MENTALK ! 1
		ECHO PLAYER You poke around by yourself in the dark corner, but don't find anything interesting here. You return to the main part of the cottage.
	ELSE
		ECHO PLAYER You follow Menelian back to the main part of the cottage.
	ENDIF
        EQUAL FLAG3 33
ENDIF

IFVAR FLAG3 = 33
        MOVE 1802
        AFFECT 1802
        EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF

;
VARIABLE MENSCRIPT
;
NUMBER 1802
NAME Menelian's Cottage
ASTRAL
RELOGIN 128
CALL 33
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The claustrophobic cottage is cluttered with a miriad of bizarre
paraphenalia. Opposite a small cot is a human skeleton, bleached
completely clean and held together with a network of wires. Anatomical
paintings are pinned to the walls, as are a variety of cryptic notes.
A menacing-looking stuffed ursine stands on its hind legs in one corner,
seeming to guard a glass case there. An overfull book shelf is above
a cluttered desk, and oaken door leads outside.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFENTRY
	IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
                ECHO ALL Menelian greets you kindly. "Come in, come in," he says. "I love speaking to travellers."
	ENDIF
	IFVAR INTNUM26 = 0
		SETEVENT 82 3 ALWAYS
		CONTEVENT 82
		ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Welcome to my home, travellers. I am but an old sage, but perhaps we might engage in some interesting discourse."
		ECHO ALL Menelian smiles.
		IFVAR INTNUM27 < 1
			ECHO ALL [To speak to Menelian, just speak normally, using a single word or simple phrase. Statements do not need punctuation, but questions should end with a question mark, i.e., 'SAGE?]
			EQUAL INTNUM27 1
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
	IFVAR INTNUM26 = 1
		ADD INTNUM26 1
		IFVAR INTNUM27 ! 2
			ECHO ALL Menelian grins. "You're back!  Please... I wish to speak to each of you seperately."%c
			ECHO ALL Menelian gestures toward a dark corner of the cottage. "Please go over there so we can discuss your journey."
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
TRAINING 17 30
TRAINING 18 30
TRAINING 23 30
TRAINING 15 10
TRAINING 32 20
TRAINING 31 20
TRAINING 20 15
;
IFSAY sage?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Yes, a sage, as you can see..."
	ECHO ALL Menelian gestures about the cottage.
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Knowledge of plants, animals and areas is my specialty, when I'm not pondering the meaning of life."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY meaning_of_life?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Yes, the meaning of life. A daunting question. Would you happen to know the meaning of life, aye or nay?"
	EQUAL MENSCRIPT 1
ENDIF
;
IFSAY aye
	IFVAR MENSCRIPT = 1
		ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Bah!  But if you truly wish to know, I have a small quest for you..."
		EQUAL MENSCRIPT 0
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFSAY nay
	IFVAR MENSCRIPT = 1
		ECHO ALL Menelian says, "I know what you mean, %n. It seems unfathomable. But if you too seek enlightenment, I have a small quest for you..."
		EQUAL MENSCRIPT 1
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFSAY quest?
	IFVAR INTNUM27 ! 2
		ECHO ALL Menelian says, "I cannot offer anything in exchange other than that we will both share in the knowledge, but I wish to know the meaning of life... There is only one other on Andor whose learning might rival my own, and that is Instadtoo. Seek her out in a place known as the Deep Realms, and ask her this question. Please return after you learn what she says!"%c
		IFNOITEM 3
			ECHO ALL Menelian says, "This should help you on your way."
			ECHO ALL Menelian drops a ragged map.
			NEWITEM 3 1578 ADJ1=254
		ENDIF
	ELSE
		ECHO ALL Menelian says, "I thank you for what you have already done."
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFSAY plants?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "I've cataloged thousands of botanical specimins. Is there are particular variety you are interested in?"
ENDIF
;
IFSAY animals?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "I have examined countless beasts, from simple animals to horrible beasts. Are you interested in creatures from the surface, of another plane or the Deep Realms?"
ENDIF
;
IFSAY areas?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The environs of Fayd can be divided into distinct areas. Fayd itself is in a grassland of rolling hills and sparse forest. To the north are the Teeth of Shartan, a vast mountain range. To the west is Grymwood, a thick forest. To the south lies the Inner Sea. Naturally, wasteland lies far to the east, north and west."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY Teeth_of_Shartan?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The Teeth of Shartan are a vast range of mountains, so named for a myth about a dragon named Shartan that tried to devour the world after the Cataclysm, and was subsequently slain by the god, Amilor."%c
	ECHO ALL Menelian continues, "There are distinct regions within the teeth of Shartan. The lower foothills are dominated by warring goblin tribes, whereas the upper mountains contain various giants, trolls and ogres. As one approaches Mirdaal, you will find other creatures such as ayeskrok, fire tigers and the ursine clans."
ENDIF
IFSAY Cataclysm?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Before the Cataclysm, only one intelligent race lived upon Andor, and that is humans."
ENDIF
IFSAY Humans?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The humans are the elder race of Andor. The technological items that can still be found are the remnants of their 'glorious' past."
ENDIF
IFSAY human?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The humans are the elder race of Andor. The technological items that can still be found are the remnants of their 'glorious' past."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY Grymwood?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A deciduous forest consisting mainly of mirmach, maple and oak. Its noteworthy inhabitants include trolls, ettins, boars, various giants spiders and wood imps. Raccoons, squirrels, deer and many birds are also prevalent. The central characteristic of the forest is the Matriarch Tree, and to the northwest is a large swamp."
ENDIF
IFSAY Matriarch_Tree?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A huge tree said to be the mother of all others in Grymwood. Unfortunately, this tree is now inhabited by Vashaska and her host of banshees."
ENDIF
IFSAY Vashaska?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Vashaska was in incredibly evil and cruel sorceress known to imprison and eat children who entered the wood. It is said that the spirits of these children now enchant places in the forest."
ENDIF
IFSAY mirmach?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A very strong tree. Its wood is excellent for construction and bowyering."
ENDIF
IFSAY oak?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A hardwood very useful for construction."
ENDIF
IFSAY maple?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A smaller tree known for its sweet sap that can be boiled to produce a luscious syrup."
ENDIF
IFSAY swamp?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The swamp to the northwest of Grymwood is dominated by a tribe of skrag. Other menaces there include giant slugs and much fiends."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY banshee?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The spirit of a cruel and evil woman, trapped in a state of undeath as punishment for her actions in life. They flock to their queen, Vashaska, in the Matriarch Tree."
ENDIF
IFSAY banshees?
	ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The spirit of a cruel and evil woman, trapped in a state of undeath as punishment for her actions in life. They flock to their queen, Vashaska, in the Matriarch Tree."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY deep_realms
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "My area of expertise is really the surface world. The authority on Deep-dwellers would be Instadtoo."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY another_plane
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "My area of expertise is really the surface world. The authority on extraplanar travel and creatures would be Instadtoo."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY surface
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Surface creatures are my specialty. Ask away."
      ECHO ALL Menelian smiles helpfully.
ENDIF
;
IFSAY kvantar?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A vile race indeed. The kvantar are the result of humanoid races, humans in particular, that have come to worship a powerful magic stone. The stone radiates some foul energy that warps their minds and bodies, instilling them with a hatred for all other life."
ENDIF
IFSAY kvantars?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A vile race indeed. The kvantar are the result of humanoid races, humans in particular, that have come to worship a powerful magic stone. The stone radiates some foul energy that warps their minds and bodies, instilling them with a hatred for all other life."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY trolls?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Trolls are stupid, overgrown brutes. They breed very rapidly, and must be kept in check. Their eyes are sought by alchemists for certain magical properties they contain."
ENDIF
IFSAY troll?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Trolls are stupid, overgrown brutes. They breed very rapidly, and must be kept in check. Their eyes are sought by alchemists for certain magical properties they contain."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY skrag?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Skrags are relatives of the trolls. They have become adapted to an aquatic environment, gaining gills and fins that allow them to maneuver in water, yet they retain the strength and stature of their land-roaming cousins. They, like many large water-dwellers, are known to be especially vulnerable to electrical attacks. Some of their body parts contain important alchemical properties, likely absorbed from the strange plants of the swamp around them."
ENDIF
IFSAY skrags?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Skrags are relatives of the trolls. They have become adapted to an aquatic environment, gaining gills and fins that allow them to maneuver in water, yet they retain the strength and stature of their land-roaming cousins. They, like many large water-dwellers, are known to be especially vulnerable to electrical attacks. Some of their body parts contain important alchemical properties, likely absorbed from the strange plants of the swamp around them."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY giant_slug?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Giant slugs are only different than the smaller variety in size. They thrive in damp terrain, and absorb nutrients by dissolving food outside their body with acid spittle. Their rubbery body makes them very immune to concussion damage."
ENDIF
IFSAY slug?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Giant slugs are only different than the smaller variety in size. They thrive in damp terrain, and absorb nutrients by dissolving food outside their body with acid spittle. Their rubbery body makes them very immune to concussion damage."
ENDIF
IFSAY slugs?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Giant slugs are only different than the smaller variety in size. They thrive in damp terrain, and absorb nutrients by dissolving food outside their body with acid spittle. Their rubbery body makes them very immune to concussion damage."
ENDIF
IFSAY giant slugs?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Giant slugs are only different than the smaller variety in size. They thrive in damp terrain, and absorb nutrients by dissolving food outside their body with acid spittle. Their rubbery body makes them very immune to concussion damage."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY muck_fiend?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Muck fiends are surely the result of some sorcerous experimentation or crossbreeding. They are unlike any other creature I have cataloged, and posess powers that are certainly magical."
ENDIF
IFSAY muck_fiends?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Muck fiends are surely the result of some sorcerous experimentation or crossbreeding. They are unlike any other creature I have cataloged, and posess powers that are certainly magical."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY goblin?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "An uncouth, cannabalistic race of ugly, green humanoids. If there is one thing I can recommend to you, it is to never make a deal with a goblin. They are pathological liars, and respect only force."
ENDIF
IFSAY goblins?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "An uncouth, cannabalistic race of ugly, green humanoids. If there is one thing I can recommend to you, it is to never make a deal with a goblin. They are pathological liars, and respect only force."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY ettin?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Ettins are a close relation to the troll. Somewhere along the line, they acquired a second head. Despite what you might think, this does not provide them with any superior intelligence."
ENDIF
IFSAY ettins?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Ettins are a close relation to the troll. Somewhere along the line, they acquired a second head. Despite what you might think, this does not provide them with any superior intelligence."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY ogre?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Basicly a smaller, more athletic variety of troll."
ENDIF
IFSAY ogres?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Basicly a smaller, more athletic variety of troll."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY viper?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A harmful snake with a poisonous bite. They are native to the wasteland."
ENDIF
IFSAY vipers?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A harmful snake with a poisonous bite. They are native to the wasteland."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY imp?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Wood imps are magical, nasty little brutes. They love to torture their victims and attack in ways that inspire fear. Though they are certainly no benefit to travellers, parts of their body are valuable spell components."
ENDIF
IFSAY imps?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Wood imps are magical, nasty little brutes. They love to torture their victims and attack in ways that inspire fear. Though they are certainly no benefit to travellers, parts of their body are valuable spell components."
ENDIF
IFSAY wood_imp?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Wood imps are magical, nasty little brutes. They love to torture their victims and attack in ways that inspire fear. Though they are certainly no benefit to travellers, parts of their body are valuable spell components."
ENDIF
IFSAY wood_imps?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Wood imps are magical, nasty little brutes. They love to torture their victims and attack in ways that inspire fear. Though they are certainly no benefit to travellers, parts of their body are valuable spell components."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY werewolf?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Werewolves are evil shapechangers, the result of a lycanthropic disease. The mindless, lesser variety of their species are the result of a greater werewolf passing on the curse to those it attacks through saliva. A lesser werewolf, if it survives long enough, will eventually advance to the greater werewolf stage where it will regain humanoid intellect. It is said that greater werewolves can mingle with society for many years before they are discovered, but eventually the \
madness of their curse will overcome them and force them into a mindless orgy of death."
ENDIF
IFSAY werewolves?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "Werewolves are evil shapechangers, the result of a lycanthropic disease. The mindless, lesser variety of their species are the result of a greater werewolf passing on the curse to those it attacks through saliva. A lesser werewolf, if it survives long enough, will eventually advance to the greater werewolf stage where it will regain humanoid intellect. It is said that greater werewolves can mingle with society for many years before they are discovered, but eventually the \
madness of their curse will overcome them and force them into a mindless orgy of death."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY giants?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "All giants are more or less the same species. The more intelligent ones are known to acquire spells. For some unknown reason, they have a hatred of all smaller creatures."
ENDIF
IFSAY giant?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "All giants are more or less the same species. The more intelligent ones are known to acquire spells. For some unknown reason, they have a hatred of all smaller creatures."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY rattlesnake?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A snake with a deadly venom distinctive for its tail, which it shakes to produce a rattling sound to scare off larger creatures."
ENDIF
IFSAY rattlesnakes?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A snake with a deadly venom distinctive for its tail, which it shakes to produce a rattling sound to scare off larger creatures."
