;
IFSAY spider?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "There are literally thousands of spider varieties. A few of the more interesting ones are the wolf spider and the phase spider, although that is only the beginning. Did you have a particular one in mind?"
ENDIF
IFSAY spiders?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "There are literally thousands of spider varieties. A few of the more interesting ones are the wolf spider and the phase spider, although that is only the beginning. Did you have a particular one in mind?"
ENDIF
;
IFSAY phase_spider?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The phase spider is one of my favorite specimins. All arachnids have some form of trap or surprise with which to ensnare their prey. Some use webs, others can jump from great distances, and some build trap doors. The phase spider is unique in this regard, for it attacks by becoming magically invisible and then striking from surprise. Combine that with the fact that the phase spider is large enough to hunt man-sized prey, and you have a truly amazing creature. Its eye is \
said to be a valuable component in certain enchantments."
ENDIF
IFSAY phase_spiders?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The phase spider is one of my favorite specimins. All arachnids have some form of trap or surprise with which to ensnare their prey. Some use webs, others can jump from great distances, and some build trap doors. The phase spider is unique in this regard, for it attacks by becoming magically invisible and then striking from surprise. Combine that with the fact that the phase spider is large enough to hunt man-sized prey, and you have a truly amazing creature. Its eye is \
said to be a valuable component in certain enchantments."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY giant_spider?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The giant spider is both friend and menace. It has little intelligence, and will attack almost anything it comes across. However, they persist mainly in places where there is much vermin, and their main diet consists of rats and other rodents. Beware their webs, which they can spin around their victim with amazing speed."
ENDIF
IFSAY giant_spiders?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The giant spider is both friend and menace. It has little intelligence, and will attack almost anything it comes across. However, they persist mainly in places where there is much vermin, and their main diet consists of rats and other rodents. Beware their webs, which they can spin around their victim with amazing speed."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY wolf_spider?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The wolf spider is about the size of a silver coin. They pose no threat to anything larger than a mouse. Instead of spinning webs, these spiders construct trap doors in the ground from which to spring upon their unwitting victims, which consist mostly of small insects."
ENDIF
IFSAY wolf_spiders?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "The wolf spider is about the size of a silver coin. They pose no threat to anything larger than a mouse. Instead of spinning webs, these spiders construct trap doors in the ground from which to spring upon their unwitting victims, which consist mostly of small insects."
ENDIF
;
IFSAY giant_rat?
      ECHO ALL Menelian says, "A single rat, or even a giant rat, is a minor threat to a person. Yet this urban threat does not persist for no reason. Consider some intriguing facts:  even a fat rat can squeeze through a hole the size of a coin, can chew its way through a brick wall in under an hour, is resistant to most diseases, and can swim for hours if need be."
ENDIF
